  "prompt": "Will there be a sufficient space for rough work in offline mode of JEE?",
  "response": "Yes, the offline mode of the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE) typically provides sufficient space for rough work. The question paper usually includes blank pages or sections specifically designated for rough work. Additionally, candidates are often allowed to bring their own pens or pencils for making calculations and notes.\n\nHowever, it's always a good idea to check the specific instructions provided by the National Testing Agency (NTA) or the relevant examination authority for the year you are taking the exam, as guidelines can vary. Make sure to follow any rules regarding what materials you can bring into the exam room for rough work.",
